var documenterSearchIndex = {"docs":
[{"category":"section","location":"library/States/#Wavefunction-types","page":"States","text":"Each of the methods implemented in this package use a unique data representation for the wavefunction. These all rely on some kind of hash table lookup, and so the following indexing schemes are defined to make this easier and faster (i.e., implemented using only stack allocated data).\n\nList of Indexing types for representing states\n\nClusterConfig\nTuckerConfig\nFockConfig\n\nEach of the different wavefunction types map different Index types to data (wavefunction coefficients)\n\nTPSCI: ClusteredState: Maps FockConfig → ClusterConfig →  Vector of coefficients (one for each state)\nBST: CompressedTuckerState: Maps FockConfig → TuckerConfig →  Tucker instance representing compressed set of coefficients for that subspace","title":"Wavefunction types"},{"category":"section","location":"library/States/#Index","page":"States","text":"Pages = [\"States.md\"]","title":"Index"},{"category":"section","location":"library/States/#Types","page":"States","text":"","title":"Types"},{"category":"section","location":"library/States/#Methods","page":"States","text":"","title":"Methods"},{"category":"method","location":"library/States/#Base.:+-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{FockConfig{N}, TPSChem.TransferConfig{N}}} where N","page":"States","text":"Base.:+(a::FockConfig, b::TransferConfig)\n\nAdd a FockConfig to a TransferConfig to get a new FockConfig\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.:+"},{"category":"method","location":"library/States/#Base.:--Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{FockConfig{N}, FockConfig{N}}} where N","page":"States","text":"Base.:-(a::FockConfig, b::FockConfig)\n\nSubtract two FockConfig's, returning a TransferConfig\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.:-"},{"category":"method","location":"library/States/#Base.:--Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{FockConfig{N}, TPSChem.TransferConfig{N}}} where N","page":"States","text":"Base.:-(a::FockConfig, b::TransferConfig)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.:-"},{"category":"section","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"Pages = [\"ActiveSpaceSolvers.md\"]","title":"ActiveSpaceSolvers"},{"category":"section","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#ActiveSpaceSolvers","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"","title":"ActiveSpaceSolvers"},{"category":"type","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"This type contains both the Ansatz and the results.\n\n- ansatz::A\n- energies::Vector{T}\n- vectors::Matrix{T}\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution"},{"category":"type","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.SolverSettings","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"This type contains the solver settings information needed to solve the problem. \n\n- nroots::Int\n- tol::Float64\n- maxiter::Int\n- verbose::Int\n- package::String [\"arpack\", \"davidson\"]\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.SolverSettings"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.SolverSettings-Tuple{}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"SolverSettings(;nroots=1, tol=1e-8, maxiter=100, verbose=0, package=\"arpack\")\n\nDefault value constructor\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.SolverSettings"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.solve-Union{Tuple{A}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{InCoreInts{T}, A, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.SolverSettings}} where {T, A<:TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Ansatz}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"solve(ints::InCoreInts{T}, ansatz::A, S::SolverSettings; v0=nothing) where {T, A<:Ansatz}\n\nGet the energies and eigenstates (stored as a Solution{A,T} type), for the Hamiltonian (defined  by ints) with the wavefunction approximated by the ansatz (defined by ansatz), and passing the  solver settings (defined by S) to the solver.\n\nArguments\n\nints: Integrals\nansatz: Subtype of the abstract type, Ansatz\nS: SolverSettings\nv0: initial guess (optional).   If provided with \"davidson\", it needs to have number of columns equal to number of roots sought.   If provided with \"arpack\", it can only be one vector.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.solve"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#LinearMaps.LinearMap-Tuple{InCoreInts, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"LinearMap(ints, prb::FCIAnsatz)\n\nGet LinearMap with takes a vector and returns action of H on that vector\n\nArguments\n\nints: InCoreInts object\nprb:  FCIAnsatz object\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"LinearMaps.LinearMap"},{"category":"type","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"Type containing all the metadata needed to define a FCI problem \n\nno::Int  # number of orbitals\nna::Int  # number of alpha\nnb::Int  # number of beta\ndima::Int \ndimb::Int \ndim::Int\nconverged::Bool\nrestarted::Bool\niteration::Int\nalgorithm::String   #  options: direct/davidson\nn_roots::Int\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"FCIAnsatz(no, na, nb)\n\nConstructor\n\nArguments\n\nno: Number of spatial orbitals\nna: Number of α electrons\nnb: Number of β electrons\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.BlockDavidson.LinOpMat-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{InCoreInts{T}, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"LinOpMat(ints, prb::FCIAnsatz)\n\nGet LinearMap with takes a vector and returns action of H on that vector\n\nArguments\n\nints: InCoreInts object\nprb:  FCIAnsatz object\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.BlockDavidson.LinOpMat"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#Base.copy!-Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.DeterminantString, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.DeterminantString}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"Base.copy!(c1::DeterminantString,c2::DeterminantString)\n\ncopy c2 into c1\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.copy!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.apply_S2_matrix-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, AbstractArray{T}}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"apply_S2_matrix(prb::FCIAnsatz, v::AbstractArray{T}) where {T}\n\nprb: FCIAnsatz just defines the current CI ansatz (i.e., fock sector)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.apply_S2_matrix"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.apply_annihilation!-Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.DeterminantString, Int64}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"apply_annihilation!(c::DeterminantString, orb_index::Int)\n\nApply an annihilation operator to c corresponding to orbital orb_index \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.apply_annihilation!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.apply_creation!-Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.DeterminantString, Int64}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"apply_creation!(c::DeterminantString, orb_index::Int)\n\nApply a creation operator to c corresponding to orbital orb_index \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.apply_creation!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.build_S2_matrix-Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"build_s2(prb::FCIAnsatz)\n\nprb: FCIAnsatz just defines the current CI ansatz (i.e., fock sector)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.build_S2_matrix"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.calc_linear_index!-Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.DeterminantString, Matrix{Int64}}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"calc_linear_index!(c::DeterminantString, binomcoeff::Array{Int,2})\n\nCalculate the linear index, passing in binomial coefficient matrix makes it much faster\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.calc_linear_index!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.calc_linear_index!-Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.DeterminantString}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"calc_linear_index!(c::DeterminantString)\n\nCalculate the linear index\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.calc_linear_index!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.calc_linear_index-Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.DeterminantString}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"calc_linear_index(c::DeterminantString)\n\nReturn linear index for lexically ordered __config DeterminantString\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.calc_linear_index"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.calc_nchk-Tuple{Integer, Integer}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"calc_nchk(n::Integer,k::Integer)\n\nCalculates binomial coefficient: n choose k\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.calc_nchk"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_1rdm-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, Vector{T}, Vector{T}}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_1rdm"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_AA-Tuple{Integer, Any, Any, Any, Any, Matrix, Matrix, Any}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_AA(no::Integer, bra_na, bra_nb, ket_na, ket_nb, bra_v::Matrix, ket_v::Matrix, spin_case)\n\nCompute represntation of 2creation operators between states bra_v and ket_v\n\nArguments\n\nno: number of orbitals\nbra_na: number of alpha electrons in bra\nbra_nb: number of beta electrons in bra\nket_na: number of alpha electrons in ket\nket_nb: number of beta electrons in ket\nbra_v: basis vectors in bra\nket_v: basis vectors ket\nspin_case: either (alpha|beta)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_AA"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_AAa-Tuple{Integer, Any, Any, Any, Any, Matrix, Matrix, Any}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_AAa(no::Integer, bra_na, bra_nb, ket_na, ket_nb, bra_v::Matrix, ket_v::Matrix, spin_case)\n\nCompute represntation of 2creation operators between states bra_v and ket_v\n\nArguments\n\nno: number of orbitals\nbra_na: number of alpha electrons in bra\nbra_nb: number of beta electrons in bra\nket_na: number of alpha electrons in ket\nket_nb: number of beta electrons in ket\nbra_v: basis vectors in bra\nket_v: basis vectors ket\nspin_case: either (alpha|beta)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_AAa"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_AB-Tuple{Integer, Any, Any, Any, Any, Matrix, Matrix}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_AB(no::Integer, bra_na, bra_nb, ket_na, ket_nb, bra_v::Matrix, ket_v::Matrix)\n\nCompute representation of p'q' operators between states bra_v and ket_v, where p is alpha and q is beta.\n\nArguments\n\nno: number of orbitals\nbra_na: number of alpha electrons in bra\nbra_nb: number of beta electrons in bra\nket_na: number of alpha electrons in ket\nket_nb: number of beta electrons in ket\nbra_v: basis vectors in bra\nket_v: basis vectors ket\n\nG(pqst) = v(IJs) <IJ|p'q'|KL> v(KLt) \n        = v(IJs) <J|<I|p'q'|K>|L> v(KLt)\n        = v(IJs) <J|<I|p'|K>q'|L> v(KLt) (-1)^N(K)\n        = v(IJs) <I|p'|K> <J|q'|L> v(KLt) (-1)^N(K)\n    \n        this can be vectorized if needed. for now:\n        loop over p,q\n            loop over K,L\n                sign = -1^N(K)\n                find indices of I,J\n                G(pq,st) += v(IJ,s) v(KL,t) * sign \n            end\n        end\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_AB"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_ABa-Tuple{Integer, Any, Any, Any, Any, Matrix, Matrix}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_ABa(no::Integer, bra_na, bra_nb, ket_na, ket_nb, bra_v::Matrix, ket_v::Matrix, spin_case)\n\nCompute represntation of 2creation operators between states bra_v and ket_v\n\nArguments\n\nno: number of orbitals\nbra_na: number of alpha electrons in bra\nbra_nb: number of beta electrons in bra\nket_na: number of alpha electrons in ket\nket_nb: number of beta electrons in ket\nbra_v: basis vectors in bra\nket_v: basis vectors ket\nspin_case: either (alpha|beta) giving ABa or BAb\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_ABa"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_ABb-Tuple{Integer, Any, Any, Any, Any, Matrix, Matrix}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_ABb(no::Integer, bra_na, bra_nb, ket_na, ket_nb, bra_v::Matrix, ket_v::Matrix, spin_case)\n\nCompute represntation of 2creation operators between states bra_v and ket_v\n\nArguments\n\nno: number of orbitals\nbra_na: number of alpha electrons in bra\nbra_nb: number of beta electrons in bra\nket_na: number of alpha electrons in ket\nket_nb: number of beta electrons in ket\nbra_v: basis vectors in bra\nket_v: basis vectors ket\nspin_case: either (alpha|beta) giving ABa or BAb\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_ABb"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_Aa-Tuple{Integer, Any, Any, Any, Any, Matrix, Matrix, Any}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_Aa(no::Integer, bra_na, bra_nb, ket_na, ket_nb, bra_v::Matrix, ket_v::Matrix, spin_case)\n\nCompute representation of a'a operators between states bra_v and ket_v\n\nArguments\n\nno: number of orbitals\nbra_na: number of alpha electrons in bra\nbra_nb: number of beta electrons in bra\nket_na: number of alpha electrons in ket\nket_nb: number of beta electrons in ket\nbra_v: basis vectors in bra\nket_v: basis vectors ket\nspin_case: either (alpha|beta)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_Aa"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_Ab-Tuple{Integer, Any, Any, Any, Any, Matrix, Matrix}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_Ab(no::Integer, bra_na, bra_nb, ket_na, ket_nb, bra_v::Matrix, ket_v::Matrix)\n\nCompute representation of p'q operators between states bra_v and ket_v, where p is alpha and q is beta.\n\nArguments\n\nno: number of orbitals\nbra_na: number of alpha electrons in bra\nbra_nb: number of beta electrons in bra\nket_na: number of alpha electrons in ket\nket_nb: number of beta electrons in ket\nbra_v: basis vectors in bra\nket_v: basis vectors ket\n\nG(pqst) = v(IJs) <IJ|p'q|KL> v(KLt) \n        = v(IJs) <J|<I|p'q|K>|L> v(KLt)\n        = v(IJs) <J|<I|p'|K>q|L> v(KLt) (-1)^N(K)\n        = v(IJs) <I|p'|K> <J|q|L> v(KLt) (-1)^N(K)\n    \n        this can be vectorized if needed. for now:\n        loop over p,q\n            loop over K,L\n                sign = -1^N(K)\n                find indices of I,J\n                G(pq,st) += v(IJ,s) v(KL,t) * sign \n            end\n        end\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_Ab"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_S2_expval-Tuple{Matrix, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_S2_expval(prb::FCIAnsatz)\n\nprb: FCIAnsatz just defines the current CI ansatz (i.e., fock sector)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_S2_expval"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_ab_terms-Tuple{Any, Any, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, Any, Any}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_ab_terms(v, H, P::FCIAnsatz, ket_a_lookup, ket_b_lookup)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_ab_terms"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_ab_terms-Tuple{Any, Any, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_ab_terms(v, H, P::FCIAnsatz)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_ab_terms"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_ab_terms2-Tuple{Any, Any, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, Any, Any}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_ab_terms2(v, H, P::FCIAnsatz, \n                      ket_a_lookup, ket_b_lookup)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_ab_terms2"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_ab_terms_full!-Tuple{Any, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, Any}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_ab_terms_full!(H, P::FCIAnsatz, Hmat)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_ab_terms_full!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_ab_terms_full-Tuple{Any, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_ab_terms_full(H, P::FCIAnsatz)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_ab_terms_full"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_creation-Tuple{Integer, Any, Any, Any, Any, Matrix, Matrix, Any}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_creation(no::Integer, bra_na, bra_nb, ket_na, ket_nb, bra_v::Matrix, ket_v::Matrix, spin_case)\n\nCompute an creation operator between states bra_v and ket_v\n\nArguments\n\nno: number of orbitals\nbra_na: number of alpha electrons in bra\nbra_nb: number of beta electrons in bra\nket_na: number of alpha electrons in ket\nket_nb: number of beta electrons in ket\nbra_v: basis vectors in bra\nket_v: basis vectors ket\nspin_case: either (alpha|beta)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_creation"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_fock_diagonal-Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, Vector, Real}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_fock_diagonal!(H, P::FCIAnsatz, e_mf::Float64)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_fock_diagonal"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_rdm1_rdm2-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, Vector{T}, Vector{T}}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_rdm1_rdm2(P::FCIAnsatz, vec_l::Vector{T}, vec_r::Vector{T}) where T\n\nCompute the 1 and 2 rdm's, in pyscf order\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_rdm1_rdm2"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_ss_terms2-Tuple{Any, Any, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, Any, Any}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_aa_terms2(v, H, P::FCIAnsatz, \n                      ket_a_lookup)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.compute_ss_terms2"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.fill_ca_lookup-Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.DeterminantString}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"fill_ca_lookup(c::DeterminantString)\n\nCreate an index table relating each DeterminantString with all ia substitutions i.e., calookup[Ka][c(p) + a(p)*np] = La\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.fill_ca_lookup"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.fill_ca_lookup2-Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.DeterminantString}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"fill_ca_lookup2(c::DeterminantString)\n\nCreate an index table relating each DeterminantString with all ia substitutions i.e., ca_lookup[Ka,p,q] = sign*La\n\n<L|p'q|K> = sign\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.fill_ca_lookup2"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.fill_ca_lookup3-Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.DeterminantString}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"fill_ca_lookup3(c::DeterminantString)\n\nCreate an index table relating each DeterminantString with all ia substitutions i.e., ca_lookup[Ka,p,q] = (sign,La)\n\n<L|p'q|K> = sign\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.fill_ca_lookup3"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.get_map-Tuple{Any, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, Any, Any}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"get_map(ham, prb::FCIAnsatz, HdiagA, HdiagB)\n\nAssumes you've already computed the spin diagonal components\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.get_map"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.get_map-Tuple{Any, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"get_map(ham, prb::FCIAnsatz)\n\nGet LinearMap with takes a vector and returns action of H on that vector\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.get_map"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.get_nchk-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"get_nchk(n::Integer,k::Integer)\n\nLooks up binomial coefficient from a precomputed table: n choose k\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.get_nchk"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.get_unoccupied!-Tuple{Vector{Int64}, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.DeterminantString}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"get_unoccupied(c::DeterminantString)\n\nget list of orbitals that are unoccupied\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.get_unoccupied!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.get_unoccupied-Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.DeterminantString}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"get_unoccupied(c::DeterminantString)\n\nget list of orbitals that are unoccupied\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.get_unoccupied"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.precompute_spin_diag_terms-Tuple{Any, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, Any}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"precompute_spin_diag_terms(H, P::FCIAnsatz, e)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.precompute_spin_diag_terms"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.reset!-Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.DeterminantString}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"reset!(c::DeterminantString)\n\nReset the DeterminantString to the first config\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.reset!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.run_fci-Tuple{Any, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"run_fci(ints, prb::FCIAnsatz)\n\ninput: ints is a struct containing 0, 2, and 4 dimensional tensors\n\nh0: energy shift\nh1: 1 electron integrals\nh2: 2 electron integrals (chemists notation)\nprb: FCIAnsatz just defines the current CI ansatz (i.e., fock sector)\n\nints is simply an InCoreInts object from TPSChem\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.run_fci"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.svd_state-Tuple{Any, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, Any, Any, Any}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"svd_state(prb::FCIAnsatz)\n\nDo an SVD of the FCI vector partitioned into clusters with (norbs1 | norbs2) where the orbitals are assumed to be ordered for cluster 1| cluster 2 haveing norbs1 and  norbs2, respectively.\n\nprb: FCIAnsatz just defines the current CI ansatz (i.e., fock sector)\nnorbs1:number of orbitals in left cluster\nnorbs2:number of orbitals in right cluster\nsvd_thresh: the threshold below which the states will be discarded\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.svd_state"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.apply_S2_matrix-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, AbstractArray{T}}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"build_S2_matrix(P::FCIAnsatz)\n\nBuild the S2 matrix in the Slater Determinant Basis  specified by P\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.apply_S2_matrix"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.apply_sminus-Tuple{Matrix, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.apply_sminus"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.apply_splus-Tuple{Matrix, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.apply_splus"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.build_H_matrix-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{InCoreInts{T}, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"build_H_matrix(ints, P::FCIAnsatz)\n\nBuild the Hamiltonian defined by ints in the Slater Determinant Basis  specified by P\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.build_H_matrix"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.build_S2_matrix-Union{Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"build_S2_matrix(P::FCIAnsatz)\n\nBuild the S2 matrix in the Slater Determinant Basis  specified by P\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.build_S2_matrix"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_1rdm-Union{Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_1rdm(sol::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}; root=1) where {T}\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_1rdm"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_1rdm_2rdm-Union{Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_2rdm(sol::Solution{A,T}; root=1) where {A,T}\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_1rdm_2rdm"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_c_a-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_operator_c_a(bra::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}, ket::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}) where {T}\n\nCompute representation of a operator between states bra_v and ket_v for alpha\n\nArguments\n\nbra: solutions for the left hand side\nket: solutions for the right hand side\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_c_a"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_c_b-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_operator_c_b(bra::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}, ket::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}) where {T}\n\nCompute representation of a operator between states bra_v and ket_v for beta \n\nArguments\n\nbra: solutions for the left hand side\nket: solutions for the right hand side\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_c_b"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_ca_aa-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_operator_ca_aa(bra::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}, ket::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}) where {T}\n\nCompute representation of a'a operators between states bra_v and ket_v for alpha-alpha\n\nArguments\n\nbra: solutions for the left hand side\nket: solutions for the right hand side\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_ca_aa"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_ca_ab-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_operator_ca_ab(bra::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}, ket::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}) where {T}\n\nCompute representation of a'a operators between states bra_v and ket_v for alpha-beta \n\nArguments\n\nbra: solutions for the left hand side\nket: solutions for the right hand side\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_ca_ab"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_ca_bb-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_operator_ca_bb(bra::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}, ket::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}) where {T}\n\nCompute representation of a'a operators between states bra_v and ket_v for beta-beta \n\nArguments\n\nbra: solutions for the left hand side\nket: solutions for the right hand side\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_ca_bb"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_cc_aa-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_operator_cc_aa(bra::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}, ket::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}) where {T}\n\nCompute representation of a'a' operators between states bra_v and ket_v for alpha-alpha \n\nArguments\n\nbra: solutions for the left hand side\nket: solutions for the right hand side\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_cc_aa"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_cc_ab-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_operator_cc_ab(bra::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}, ket::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}) where {T}\n\nCompute representation of a'a' operators between states bra_v and ket_v for alpha-beta \n\nArguments\n\nbra: solutions for the left hand side\nket: solutions for the right hand side\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_cc_ab"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_cc_bb-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_operator_cc_aa(bra::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}, ket::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}) where {T}\n\nCompute representation of a'a' operators between states bra_v and ket_v for beta-beta \n\nArguments\n\nbra: solutions for the left hand side\nket: solutions for the right hand side\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_cc_bb"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_cca_aaa-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_operator_cca_aaa(bra::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}, ket::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}) where {T}\n\nCompute representation of a'a'a operators between states bra_v and ket_v for alpha-alpha-alpha \n\nArguments\n\nbra: solutions for the left hand side\nket: solutions for the right hand side\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_cca_aaa"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_cca_aba-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_operator_cca_aba(bra::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}, ket::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}) where {T}\n\nCompute representation of a'a'a operators between states bra_v and ket_v for alpha-beta-alpha \n\nArguments\n\nbra: solutions for the left hand side\nket: solutions for the right hand side\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_cca_aba"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_cca_abb-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_operator_cca_abb(bra::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}, ket::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}) where {T}\n\nCompute representation of a'a'a operators between states bra_v and ket_v for alpha-beta-beta \n\nArguments\n\nbra: solutions for the left hand side\nket: solutions for the right hand side\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_cca_abb"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_cca_bbb-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}, TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"compute_operator_cca_bbb(bra::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}, ket::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T}) where {T}\n\nCompute representation of a'a'a operators between states bra_v and ket_v for beta-beta-beta \n\nArguments\n\nbra: solutions for the left hand side\nket: solutions for the right hand side\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_operator_cca_bbb"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_s2-Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution}","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_s2(sol::Solution)\n\nCompute the <S^2> expectation values for each state in sol\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.compute_s2"},{"category":"method","location":"library/ActiveSpaceSolvers/#TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.svd_state-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.Solution{TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.FCI.FCIAnsatz, T}, Any, Any, Any}} where T","page":"ActiveSpaceSolvers","text":"svd_state(sol::Solution{FCIAnsatz,T},norbs1,norbs2,svd_thresh; root=1) where T\n\nDo an SVD of the FCI vector partitioned into clusters with (norbs1 | norbs2) where the orbitals are assumed to be ordered for cluster 1| cluster 2 haveing norbs1 and  norbs2, respectively.\n\nsol: Solution just defines the current CI states \nnorbs1:number of orbitals in left cluster\nnorbs2:number of orbitals in right cluster\nsvd_thresh: the threshold below which the states will be discarded\nroot: which root to SVD\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ActiveSpaceSolvers.svd_state"},{"category":"section","location":"library/ClusteredStates/","page":"ClusteredStates","text":"Pages = [\"ClusteredStates.md\"]","title":"ClusteredStates"},{"category":"section","location":"library/ClusteredStates/#ClusteredStates","page":"ClusteredStates","text":"","title":"ClusteredStates"},{"category":"section","location":"installation_instructions/#TPSChem","page":"Installation Instructions","text":"A Julia package for course-grained electronic structure calculations","title":"TPSChem"},{"category":"section","location":"installation_instructions/#Installation","page":"Installation Instructions","text":"Download\n\ngit clone https://github.com/nmayhall/TPSChem.jl\ncd TPSChem\n\nTesting\n\njulia --project=./ -tauto\nusing TPSChem\nusing Pkg\nPkg.test()","title":"Installation"},{"category":"section","location":"cmf/#Cluster-Mean-Field-Calculation-(CMF)","page":"Cluster Mean-Field Calculation (CMF)","text":"In this example, we cluster a sequence of H<sub>2</sub> molecules and solve them self-consistently","title":"Cluster Mean-Field Calculation (CMF)"},{"category":"section","location":"cmf/#First-create-a-molecule","page":"Cluster Mean-Field Calculation (CMF)","text":"using TPSChem\n\natoms = []\npush!(atoms,Atom(1,\"H\",[0,0,0]))\npush!(atoms,Atom(2,\"H\",[0,0,1]))\npush!(atoms,Atom(3,\"H\",[0,0,2]))\npush!(atoms,Atom(4,\"H\",[0,0,3]))\npush!(atoms,Atom(5,\"H\",[0,0,4]))\npush!(atoms,Atom(6,\"H\",[0,0,5]))\nbasis = \"sto-3g\"\n\nNow create a PySCF object for creating integrals, and run FCI with 3 alpha and 3 beta electrons\n\nmol  = Molecule(0,1,atoms)\nmf   = TPSChem.pyscf_do_scf(mol,basis)\nints = TPSChem.pyscf_build_ints(mf.mol,mf.mo_coeff);\n\nna = 3\nnb = 3\ne_fci, d1_fci, d2_fci = TPSChem.pyscf_fci(ints,na,nb)\nC = mf.mo_coeff\nrdm_mf = C[:,1:2] * C[:,1:2]'\n\nLocalize the orbitals and print to molden file for viewing\n\nCl = TPSChem.localize(mf.mo_coeff,\"lowdin\",mf)\nTPSChem.pyscf_write_molden(mol,basis,Cl,filename=\"lowdin.molden\")\nS = TPSChem.get_ovlp(mf)\nU =  C' * S * Cl\n\nRotate the integrals to this new localized basis\n\nints = TPSChem.orbital_rotation(ints,U)\n\nNow we need to specify a clustering\n\nclusters    = [(1:2),(3:4),(5:6)]\ninit_fspace = [(1,1),(1,1),(1,1)]\n\nclusters = [Cluster(i,collect(clusters[i])) for i = 1:length(clusters)]\ndisplay(clusters)\n\nrdm1 = zeros(size(ints.h1))\nrdm1a = rdm_mf*.5\nrdm1b = rdm_mf*.5\n\n\nNow run the orbital optimization and dump the resultinging orbitals \n\nU = TPSChem.cmf_oo(ints, clusters, init_fspace, rdm1, verbose=0, gconv=1e-6)\n\nC_cmf = Cl*U\n\nTPSChem.pyscf_write_molden(mol,basis,C_cmf,filename=\"cmf.molden\")","title":"First create a molecule"},{"category":"section","location":"library/BST/#BST","page":"BST","text":"The Block-Sparse Tucker (BST) method, approximates FCI as a linear combination of individually compressed (via HOSVD) blocks of the Hilbert space.","title":"BST"},{"category":"section","location":"library/BST/#Background","page":"BST","text":"Similar to TPSCI, the approach here starts with a CMF wavefunction, and systematically reintroduces the discarded tensor product states to variationally approach FCI. Unlike with TPSCI, however, we don't assume that the final wavefunction is written as  a purely sparse form (where only a few TPS's are needed), but rather we assume that collections of TPS's where certain numbers of clusters are \"excited\" can be efficiently compressed via HOSVD (although the basic idea would extend to other tensor decompositions, like CP or MPS). ","title":"Background"},{"category":"section","location":"library/BST/#Performance-considerations","page":"BST","text":"","title":"Performance considerations"},{"category":"section","location":"library/BST/#Index","page":"BST","text":"Pages   = [\"BST.md\"]","title":"Index"},{"category":"section","location":"library/BST/#Documentation","page":"BST","text":"","title":"Documentation"},{"category":"section","location":"library/BST/#HOSVD","page":"BST","text":"","title":"HOSVD"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.build_sigma!-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{BSTstate{T, N, R}, BSTstate{T, N, R}, Any, Any}} where {T, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"build_sigma_parallel!(sigma_vector::BSTstate, ci_vector::BSTstate, cluster_ops, clustered_ham)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.build_sigma!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.build_sigma_cepa!-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{BSTstate{T, N, R}, BSTstate{T, N, R}, Any, Any}} where {T, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"build_sigma_cepa!(sigma_vector, ci_vector, cluster_ops, clustered_ham)\n\nThread-safe version of build_sigma! for use in CEPA matvec. Uses per-task scratch allocation to avoid races with Julia's dynamic scheduler.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.build_sigma_cepa!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.build_sigma_serial!-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{BSTstate{T, N, R}, BSTstate{T, N, R}, Any, Any}} where {T, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"build_sigma!(sigma_vector::BSTstate, ci_vector::BSTstate, cluster_ops, clustered_ham)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.build_sigma_serial!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.cache_hamiltonian_old-Tuple{BSTstate, BSTstate, Any, Any}","page":"BST","text":"build_sigma!(sigma_vector::BSTstate, ci_vector::BSTstate, cluster_ops, clustered_ham)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.cache_hamiltonian_old"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.build_compressed_1st_order_state-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{BSTstate{T, N, R}, Any, Any}} where {T, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"build_compressed_1st_order_state(ψ::BSTstate{T,N,R}, cluster_ops, clustered_ham; \nthresh=1e-7, \nmax_number=nothing, \nnbody=4, \nprescreen=false,\ncompress_twice=true\n)  where {T,N,R}\n\nTBW\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.build_compressed_1st_order_state"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.build_compressed_1st_order_state_old-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{BSTstate{T, N, R}, Any, Any}} where {T, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"build_compressed_1st_order_state_old(ket_cts::BSTstate{T,N,R}, cluster_ops, clustered_ham; \n    thresh=1e-7, \n    max_number=nothing, \n    nbody=4, \n    compress_twice=true) where {T,N,R}\n    thresh=1e-7, \n    max_number=nothing, \n    nbody=4) where {T,N}\n\nApply the Hamiltonian to v expanding into the uncompressed space. This is done only partially, where each term is recompressed after being computed. Lots of overhead probably from compression, but never completely uncompresses.\n\n#Arguments\n\ncts::BSTstate: input state\ncluster_ops:\nclustered_ham: Hamiltonian\nthresh: Threshold for each HOSVD \nmax_number: max number of tucker factors kept in each HOSVD\nnbody: allows one to limit (max 4body) terms in the Hamiltonian considered\ncompress_twice: Should we recompress after adding the tuckers together\n\n#Returns\n\nv1::BSTstate\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.build_compressed_1st_order_state_old"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.ci_solve-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{BSTstate{T, N, R}, Any, Any}} where {T, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"function ci_solve(ci_vector_in::BSTstate{T,N,R}, cluster_ops, clustered_ham; \n                     conv_thresh = 1e-5,\n                     max_ss_vecs = 12,\n                     max_iter    = 40,\n                     shift       = nothing,\n                     precond     = false,\n                     verbose     = 0,\n                     solver      = \"davidson\") where {T,N,R}\n\nSolve for ground state in the space spanned by ci_vector's compression vectors\n\nArguments\n\nconv_thresh: residual convergence threshold\nmax_ss_vecs: max number of subspace vectors\nmax_iter: Max iterations in solver\nshift:  Use a shift? this is for CEPA type \nprecond: use preconditioner? Only applied to Davidson and not yet working,\nverbose: print level\nsolver: Which solver to use. Options = [\"davidson\", \"krylovkit\"]\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ci_solve"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.define_foi_space-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{T, Any}} where T<:Union{BSTstate, TPSChem.BSstate}","page":"BST","text":"define_foi_space(v::BSTstate, clustered_ham; nbody=2)\n\nCompute the first-order interacting space as defined by clustered_ham\n\n#Arguments\n\nv::BSTstate: input state\nclustered_ham: Hamiltonian\nnbody: allows one to limit (max 4body) terms in the Hamiltonian considered\n\n#Returns\n\nfoi::OrderedDict{FockConfig,Vector{TuckerConfig}}\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.define_foi_space"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.get_map-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{BSTstate{T, N, R}, Any, Any}} where {T, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"get_map(ci_vector::BSTstate, cluster_ops, clustered_ham)\n\nGet LinearMap with takes a vector and returns action of H on that vector\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.get_map"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.project_out!-Union{Tuple{Rw}, Tuple{Rv}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{BSTstate{T, N, Rv}, BSTstate{T, N, Rw}}} where {T, N, Rv, Rw}","page":"BST","text":"project_out!(v::BSTstate, w::BSTstate; thresh=1e-16)\n\nProject w out of v  |v'> = |v> - |w><w|v>\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.project_out!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.tucker_cepa_solve-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{BSTstate{T, N, R}, BSTstate, Any, Any}, Tuple{BSTstate{T, N, R}, BSTstate, Any, Any, Any}, Tuple{BSTstate{T, N, R}, BSTstate, Vararg{Any, 4}}} where {T, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"tucker_cepa_solve!(ref_vector::BSTstate, cepa_vector::BSTstate, cluster_ops, clustered_ham; tol=1e-5, cache=true)\n\nArguments\n\nref_vector: Input reference state. \ncepa_vector: BSTstate which defines the configurational space defining {X}. This \n\nshould be the first-order interacting space (or some compressed version of it).\n\ncluster_ops\nclustered_ham\ntol: haven't yet set this up (NYI)\ncache: Should we cache the compressed H operators? Speeds up drastically, but uses lots of memory\n\nCompute compressed CEPA. Since there can be non-zero overlap with a multireference state, we need to generalize.\n\nHC = SCe\n\n|Haa + Hax| |1 | = |I   + Sax| |1 | E\n|Hxa + Hxx| |Cx|   |Sxa + I  | |Cx|\n\nHaa + Hax*Cx = (1 + Sax*Cx)E\nHxa + HxxCx = SxaE + CxE\n\nThe idea for CEPA is to approximate E in the amplitude equation. CEPA(0): E = Eref\n\n(Hxx-Eref)*Cx = Sxa*Eref - Hxa\n\nAx=b\n\nAfter solving, the Energy can be obtained as:\n\nE = (Eref + Hax*Cx) / (1 + Sax*Cx)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.tucker_cepa_solve"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.tucker_cepa_solve2-Tuple{BSTstate, BSTstate, Any, Any}","page":"BST","text":"tucker_cepa_solve!(ref_vector::BSTstate, cepa_vector::BSTstate, cluster_ops, clustered_ham; tol=1e-5, cache=true)\n\nArguments\n\nref_vector: Input reference state. \ncepa_vector: BSTstate which defines the configurational space defining {X}. This \n\nshould be the first-order interacting space (or some compressed version of it).\n\ncluster_ops\nclustered_ham\ntol: haven't yet set this up (NYI)\ncache: Should we cache the compressed H operators? Speeds up drastically, but uses lots of memory\n\nCompute compressed CEPA. Since there can be non-zero overlap with a multireference state, we need to generalize.\n\nHC = SCe\n\n|Haa + Hax| |1 | = |I   + Sax| |1 | E |Hxa + Hxx| |Cx|   |Sxa + I  | |Cx|\n\nHaa + HaxCx = (1 + SaxCx)E Hxa + HxxCx = SxaE + CxE\n\nThe idea for CEPA is to approximate E in the amplitude equation. CEPA(0): E = Eref\n\n(Hxx-Eref)Cx = SxaEref - Hxa\n\nAx=b\n\nAfter solving, the Energy can be obtained as: E = (Eref + HaxCx) / (1 + SaxCx)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.tucker_cepa_solve2"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.block_sparse_tucker-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{BSTstate{T, N, R}, Any, Any}} where {T, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"block_sparse_tucker(input_vec::BSTstate{T,N,R}, cluster_ops, clustered_ham;\n                    max_iter=20,\n                    nbody=4,\n                    H0=\"Hcmf\",\n                    thresh_var=1e-4,\n                    thresh_foi=1e-6,\n                    thresh_pt=1e-5,\n                    thresh_spin=nothing,\n                    ci_conv=1e-5,\n                    ci_max_iter=50,\n                    ci_max_ss_vecs=12,\n                    ci_lindep_thresh=1e-10,\n                    resolve_ss=false,\n                    do_pt=true,\n                    tol_tucker=1e-6,\n                    solver=\"davidson\",\n                    verbose=1) where {T,N,R}\n\nArguments\n\ninput_vec::BSTstate: initial state\ncluster_ops: local cluster operators\nclustered_ham::ClusteredOperator: hamiltonian\nmax_iter = 20: max number of iterations\nnbody = 4: include up to nbody terms when forming the FOIS to search\nH0 = \"Hcmf\": zeroth-order hamiltonian for computing 1st order wavefunction [\"Hcmf\", \"H\"]\nnbody: max number of nbody terms in the Hamiltonian used for creating FOIS\nthresh_var: Compression threshold for the variational solution\nthresh_foi: Compression threshold for the FOIS\nthresh_pt: Compression threshold for the first-order wavefunction (if used)\nthresh_spin: Compression threshold for adding S2 residual, only does this if thresh is specified\nci_conv:     Convergence threshold for the CI (norm of residual)\nci_max_iter:    max iterations for CI problem\nci_max_ss_vecs: max number of subspace vectors for lanczos/davidson\nresolve_ss:  After compressing previous variational state, should we resolve in new subspace?\ndo_pt = true: Compute pt1 wavefunction for finding updated compression basis?\ntol_tucker: Convergence threshold for Tucker iterations (energy change)\nsolver:\nverbose: How much to print? \n\nReturns\n\ne_var::Float64: the final variational energy\nv_var::BSTstate: the final variational state\n\nSee also: BSTstate, Tucker\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.block_sparse_tucker"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.block_sparse_tucker_old-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{BSTstate{T, N, R}, Any, Any}} where {T, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"function block_sparse_tucker(input_vec::BSTstate{T,N,R}, cluster_ops, clustered_ham;\n    max_iter        = 20,\n    max_iter_pt     = 200, # max number of iterations for solving for PT1\n    nbody           = 4,\n    H0              = \"Hcmf\",\n    thresh_var      = 1e-4,\n    thresh_foi      = 1e-6,\n    thresh_pt       = 1e-5,\n    ci_conv         = 1e-5,\n    ci_max_iter     = 50,\n    ci_max_ss_vecs  = 12,\nresolve_ss      = false,\n    do_pt           = true,\n    tol_tucker      = 1e-6 ) where {T,N,R}\n\nArguments\n\ninput_vec::BSTstate: initial state\ncluster_ops: local cluster operators\nclustered_ham::ClusteredOperator: hamiltonian\nmax_iter = 20: max number of iterations\nmax_iter_pt = 200: max number of iterations to solve for the 1st order wavefunction\nnbody = 4: include up to nbody terms when forming the FOIS to search\nH0 = \"Hcmf\": zeroth-order hamiltonian for computing 1st order wavefunction [\"Hcmf\", \"H\"]\nnbody: max number of nbody terms in the Hamiltonian used for creating FOIS\nthresh_var: Compression threshold for the variational solution\nthresh_foi: Compression threshold for the FOIS\nthresh_pt: Compression threshold for the first-order wavefunction (if used)\nci_conv:     Convergence threshold for the CI (norm of residual)\nci_max_iter:    max iterations for CI problem\nci_max_ss_vecs: max number of subspace vectors for lanczos/davidson\nresolve_ss:  After compressing previous variational state, should we resolve in new subspace?\ndo_pt = true: Compute pt1 wavefunction for finding updated compression basis?\ntol_tucker: Convergence threshold for Tucker iterations (energy change)\nsolver: \n\nReturns\n\ne_var::Float64: the final variational energy\nv_var::BSTstate: the final variational state\n\nSee also: BSTstate, Tucker\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.block_sparse_tucker_old"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.compute_expectation_value-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{BSTstate{T, N, R}, Any, ClusteredOperator}} where {T, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"function compute_expectation_value(ci_vector::BSTstate{T,N,R}, cluster_ops, clustered_op::TPSChem.ClusteredOperator; nbody) where {T,N,R}\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.compute_expectation_value"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.compute_spin_residual-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{BSTstate{T, N, R}, Any}} where {T, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"compute_spin_residual(v::BSTstate{T,N,R}, cluster_ops, thresh) where {T,N,R}\n\nCompute |r> = S2|v> - |v><v|S2|v>\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.compute_spin_residual"},{"category":"type","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.Tucker","page":"BST","text":"Simple Tucker (HOSVD) type\n\nData\n\ncore::Array{T, N}\nfactors::NTuple{N, Matrix{T}}\n\nTucker factors are stored as tall matrices the core tensor is actually a list of core tensors, to enable multistate calculations\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.Tucker"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.Tucker-Union{Tuple{TPSChem.Tucker{TT, NN, RR}}, Tuple{RR}, Tuple{NN}, Tuple{TT}} where {TT, NN, RR}","page":"BST","text":"function Tucker(t::Tucker{T,N,R}, n_roots::Integer) where {T,N,R}\n\nCreate a new Tucker with a different number of core tensors; R=n_roots. New core tensors added are initialized to zero.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.Tucker"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#Base.:+-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{NTuple{R, Array}, NTuple{R, Array}}} where R","page":"BST","text":"Base.:(+)(t1::NTuple{R,Array}, t2::NTuple{R,Array}) where R\n\nTBW\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.:+"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.add!-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{NTuple{R, AbstractArray}, NTuple{R, AbstractArray}}} where R","page":"BST","text":"add!(t1::NTuple{R,Array}, t2::NTuple{R,Array}) where R\n\nTBW\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.add!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.add_transformed_tensor-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{Array{T, N}, NTuple{N, Matrix{T}}, Array{T, N}, Array{Vector{T}, 1}}} where {T<:Number, N}","page":"BST","text":"add_transformed_tensor(v::Array{T,N}, transforms::NTuple{N,Matrix{T}}, out::Array{T,N}, scr::Vector{Vector{T}}; trans=false) where {T<:Number,N}\n\nTransform a tensor (v) by a sequence of matrices (transforms).  This version takes in a set of scratch arrays (scr), one for each index in the tensor\n\nout(IJK) += v(ijk) U(Ii) U(Jj) U(Kk) \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.add_transformed_tensor"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.compress-Union{Tuple{TPSChem.Tucker{T, N, R}}, Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}} where {T, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"compress(t::Tucker{T,N}; thresh=1e-7, max_number=nothing) where {T,N}\n\nTry to compress further \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.compress"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.nonorth_add-Union{Tuple{Array{TPSChem.Tucker{T, N, R}, 1}}, Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}} where {T<:Number, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"nonorth_add(tucks::Vector{Tucker{T,N}}; thresh=1e-10, max_number=nothing) where {T,N}\n\nAdd together multiple Tucker instances. Assumed non-orthogonal.\n\nArguments\n\ntucks::Vector{Tucker{T,N}}: Vector of Tucker objects\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.nonorth_add"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.nonorth_dot-Union{Tuple{R2}, Tuple{R1}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.Tucker{T, N, R1}, TPSChem.Tucker{T, N, R2}, Any, Any}} where {T, N, R1, R2}","page":"BST","text":"function nonorth_dot(t1::Tucker{T,N,R}, t2::Tucker{T,N,R}) where {T,N,R}\n\nNote: This doesn't assume t1 and t2 have the same compression vectors \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.nonorth_dot"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.nonorth_dot-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.Tucker{T, N, R}, TPSChem.Tucker{T, N, R}}} where {T, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"function nonorth_dot(t1::Tucker{T,N,R}, t2::Tucker{T,N,R}) where {T,N,R}\n\nNote: This doesn't assume t1 and t2 have the same compression vectors \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.nonorth_dot"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.nonorth_overlap-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.Tucker{T, N, R}, TPSChem.Tucker{T, N, R}}} where {T, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"function nonorth_overlap(t1::Tucker{T,N,R}, t2::Tucker{T,N,R}) where {T,N,R}\n\nNote: This doesn't assume t1 and t2 have the same compression vectors. Returns RxR overlap matrix \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.nonorth_overlap"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.orth_dot-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.Tucker{T, N, R}, TPSChem.Tucker{T, N, R}}} where {T, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"function orth_dot(t1::Tucker{T,N,R}, t2::Tucker{T,N,R}) where {T,N,R}\n\nNote: This assumes t1 and t2 have the same compression vectors \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.orth_dot"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.scale!-Tuple{TPSChem.Tucker, Any}","page":"BST","text":"scale!(t1::Tucker, a)\n\nTBW\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.scale!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.scale-Tuple{TPSChem.Tucker, Any}","page":"BST","text":"scale(t1::Tucker, a)\n\nTBW\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.scale"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.transform_basis!-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.Tucker{T, N, R}, Array{Matrix{T}, 1}}} where {T, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"transform_basis!(tuck::Tucker{T,N,R}, transform_list::Vector{Matrix{T}}) where {T,N,R}\n\nTBW\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.transform_basis!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.transform_basis-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{Array{T, N}, NTuple{N, Matrix{T}}}} where {T<:Number, N}","page":"BST","text":"transform_basis(v::Array{T,N}, transforms::NTuple{N,Matrix{T}}; trans=false) where {T<:Number,N}\n\nTBW\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.transform_basis"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.tucker_decompose-Union{Tuple{NTuple{R, Array{T, N}}}, Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}} where {T, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"function tucker_decompose(A::Array{T,N}; thresh=1e-7, max_number=nothing, verbose=1, type=\"magnitude\") where {T,N}\n\nTucker Decomposition of dense tensor:      A ~ X *(1) U1 *(2) U2 .... where cluster states are discarded based on the corresponding SVD #Arguments\n\nA: matrix to decompose\nthresh: threshold for discarding tucker factors\nmax_number: limit number of tucker factors to this value\ntype: type of trunctation. \"magnitude\" discards values smaller than this number.    \"sum\" discards values such that the sum of discarded values is smaller than thresh.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.tucker_decompose"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.tucker_initialize-Union{Tuple{NTuple{R, Array{T, N}}}, Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}} where {T, N, R}","page":"BST","text":"function tucker_decompose(A::Array{T,N}; num_roots=nothing, max_number=nothing, verbose=1, type=\"magnitude\") where {T,N}\n\nTucker Decomposition of dense tensor:      A ~ X *(1) U1 *(2) U2 .... where cluster states are discarded based on the corresponding SVD #Arguments\n\nA: matrix to decompose\nnum_roots: number of roots to keep \nmax_number: limit number of tucker factors to this value\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.tucker_initialize"},{"category":"method","location":"library/BST/#TPSChem.tucker_recompose-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"BST","text":"tucker_recompose(core, factors)\n\nRecompose Tucker Decomposition \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.tucker_recompose"},{"category":"section","location":"library/CMFs/#CMF","page":"CMF","text":"","title":"CMF"},{"category":"section","location":"library/CMFs/#Background","page":"CMF","text":"The Cluster Mean Field (CMF) approach used in this work was developed by Jimènez-Hoyos and Scuseria. \n\nPySCF-backed helpers (pyscf_do_scf, pyscf_build_ints, ...) are provided by the package extension TPSChemPyCallExt, which activates when PyCall is loaded.","title":"Background"},{"category":"section","location":"library/CMFs/#Index","page":"CMF","text":"Pages = [\"CMFs.md\"]","title":"Index"},{"category":"section","location":"library/CMFs/#Documentation","page":"CMF","text":"","title":"Documentation"},{"category":"method","location":"library/CMFs/#TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.assemble_full_rdm-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Vector{MOCluster}, Dict{Integer, TPSChem.RDM.RDM1{T}}, Dict{Integer, TPSChem.RDM.RDM2{T}}}} where T","page":"CMF","text":"assemble_full_rdm(clusters::Vector{MOCluster}, rdm1s::Dict{Integer, Array}, rdm2s::Dict{Integer, Array})\n\nReturn full system 1 and 2 RDMs\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.assemble_full_rdm"},{"category":"method","location":"library/CMFs/#TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.assemble_full_rdm-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Vector{MOCluster}, Dict{Integer, TPSChem.RDM.RDM1{T}}}} where T","page":"CMF","text":"assemble_full_rdm(clusters::Vector{MOCluster}, rdm1s::Dict{Integer, RDM1{T}}) where T\n\nReturn spin summed 1 and 2 RDMs\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.assemble_full_rdm"},{"category":"method","location":"library/CMFs/#TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.cmf_ci-Tuple{Any, Any, Any, TPSChem.RDM.RDM1}","page":"CMF","text":"cmf_ci(ints, clusters, fspace, in_rdm1::RDM1; \n            maxiter_ci  = 100, \n            maxiter_d1  = 20, \n            tol_d1      = 1e-6, \n            tol_ci      = 1e-8, \n            verbose     = 1,\n            sequential  = false)\n\nOptimize the 1RDM for CMF-CI\n\n#Arguments\n\nints::InCoreInts: integrals for full system\nclusters::Vector{MOCluster}: vector of cluster objects\nfspace::Vector{Vector{Integer}}: vector of particle number occupations for each cluster specifying the sectors of fock space \nin_rdm1: initial guess for 1particle density matrix\ntol_d1: Convergence threshold for change in density \ntol_ci: Convergence threshold for the cluster CI problems \nmaxiter_d1: Max number of iterations for density optimization\nmaxiter_ci: Max number of iterations for CI diagonalization\nsequential: Use the density matrix of the previous cluster in a cMF iteration to form effective integrals. Improves comvergence, may depend on cluster orderings   \nverbose: Printing level \n\nReturns\n\ne: Energy\nrdm1_dict: Dictionary of 1RDMs; cluster index –> RDM1\nrdm2_dict: Dictionary of 2RDMs; cluster index –> RDM2\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.cmf_ci"},{"category":"method","location":"library/CMFs/#TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.cmf_ci-Tuple{Molecule, Matrix, Vector{MOCluster}, Vector, Any, Any}","page":"CMF","text":"cmf_ci(mol::Molecule, C::Matrix, clusters::Vector{MOCluster}, fspace::Vector, dguess; \n        max_iter=10, dconv=1e-6, econv=1e-10, verbose=1)\n\nOptimize the 1RDM for CMF-CI, without requiring an InCoreInts object \n\nArguments\n\nmol::Molecule: a Molecule type\nC: MO coefficients for full system (spin restricted)\nclusters::Vector{MOCluster}: vector of MOCluster objects\nfspace::Vector{Vector{Integer}}: vector of particle number occupations for each cluster specifying the sectors of fock space \ndguess: initial guess for 1particle density matrix (spin summed) \ndconv: Convergence threshold for change in density \neconv: Convergence threshold for change in energy \nverbose: how much to print\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.cmf_ci"},{"category":"method","location":"library/CMFs/#TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.cmf_ci_iteration-Tuple{Molecule, Vararg{Any, 5}}","page":"CMF","text":"cmf_ci_iteration(mol::Molecule, C, rdm1a, rdm1b, clusters, fspace; \n                 verbose=1)\n\nPerform single CMF-CI iteration, returning new energy, and density. This method forms the eri's on the fly to avoid global N^4 storage\n\nArguments\n\nmol::Molecule: a Molecule type\nC: MO coefficients for full system (spin restricted)\nrdm1a: 1particle density matrix (alpha) \nrdm1b: 1particle density matrix (beta) \nclusters::Vector{MOCluster}: vector of MOCluster objects\nfspace::Vector{Vector{Int}}: vector of particle number occupations for each cluster specifying the sectors of fock space \nverbose: how much to print\nci_max_iter: How many FCI iterations do we allow for each cluster. Default=40\nci_conv_tol: How what is the convergence (gradient norm) for the FCI on each cluster. Default=1e-8 \n\nSee also: cmf_ci_iteration\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.cmf_ci_iteration"},{"category":"method","location":"library/CMFs/#TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.cmf_ci_iteration-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{InCoreInts{T}, Vector{MOCluster}, TPSChem.RDM.RDM1{T}, Any}} where T","page":"CMF","text":"cmf_ci_iteration(ints::InCoreInts{T}, clusters::Vector{MOCluster}, in_rdm1::RDM1{T}, fspace; \n                      use_pyscf = false, \n                      verbose   = 1, \n                      sequential= false, \n                      spin_avg  = true, \n                      tol_ci    = 1e-8,\n                      maxiter_ci    = 100\n) where T\n\nPerform single CMF-CI iteration, returning new energy, and density\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.cmf_ci_iteration"},{"category":"method","location":"library/CMFs/#TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.cmf_oo-Tuple{Molecule, Matrix, Vector{MOCluster}, Any, Any}","page":"CMF","text":"cmf_oo(mol::Molecule, Cguess::Matrix, clusters::Vector{MOCluster}, fspace, dguess; \n        max_iter_oo=100, max_iter_ci=100, gconv=1e-6, verbose=0, method=\"bfgs\")\n\nDo CMF with orbital optimization with on the fly integrals\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.cmf_oo"},{"category":"method","location":"library/CMFs/#TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.cmf_oo-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{InCoreInts{T}, Vector{MOCluster}, Any, TPSChem.RDM.RDM1{T}}} where T","page":"CMF","text":"cmf_oo(ints::InCoreInts{T}, clusters::Vector{MOCluster}, fspace, dguess::RDM1{T}; \n            max_iter_oo=100, \n            max_iter_ci=100, \n            gconv=1e-6, \n            verbose=0, \n            method=\"bfgs\", \n            alpha=nothing,\n            sequential=false) where T\n\nDo CMF with orbital optimization\n\n#Arguments\n\nints::InCoreInts: integrals for full system\nclusters::Vector{MOCluster}: vector of cluster objects\nfspace::Vector{Vector{Integer}}: vector of particle number occupations for each cluster specifying the sectors of fock space \ndguess_a: initial guess for 1particle density matrix\nmax_iter_oo: Max iter for the orbital optimization iterations \nmax_iter_ci: Max iter for the cmf iteration for the cluster states \ngconv: Convergence threshold for change in gradient of energy \nsequential: If true use the density matrix of the previous cluster in a cMF iteration to form effective integrals. Improves comvergence, may depend on cluster orderings   \nverbose: Printing level \nmethod: optimization method\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.cmf_oo"},{"category":"method","location":"library/CMFs/#TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.cmf_oo_diis-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{InCoreInts{T}, Vector{MOCluster}, Any, TPSChem.RDM.RDM1{T}}} where T","page":"CMF","text":"cmf_oo_diis( ints_in::InCoreInts{T}, clusters::Vector{MOCluster}, fspace, dguess::RDM1{T}; \n                maxiter_oo      = 100, \n                maxiter_ci      = 100, \n                maxiter_d1      = 100, \n                tol_oo          = 1e-6, \n                tol_d1          = 1e-7, \n                tol_ci          = 1e-8, \n                verbose         = 0, \n                max_ss_size     = 8, \n                diis_start      = 1,\n                alpha           = .1,\n                zero_intra_rots = true \n                sequential      = false\n                ) where T\n\nDo CMF with orbital optimization using DIIS\n\nArguments\n\nints::InCoreInts: integrals for full system\nclusters::Vector{MOCluster}: vector of cluster objects\nfspace::Vector{Vector{Integer}}: vector of particle number occupations for each cluster specifying the sectors of fock space \ndguess: initial guess for 1particle density matrix\nmaxiter_oo: Max iter for the orbital optimization iterations \nmaxiter_d1: Max iter for the cmf iteration for the 1RDM \nmaxiter_ci: Max iter for the CI diagonalization of the cluster states \ntol_oo: Convergence threshold for change in orbital gradient \ntol_ci: Convergence threshold for the cluster CI problems \ntol_d1: Convergence threshold for the CMF 1RDM \nsequential: If true use the density matrix of the previous cluster in a cMF iteration to form effective integrals. Improves comvergence, may depend on cluster orderings   \nverbose: Printing level \nmax_ss_size: Max number of DIIS vectors\ndiis_start: When to start doing DIIS extrapolations\nalpha: New vector added to ss is k=-alpha*g where g is the orbital gradient. This should be improved with Hessian.\nzero_intra_rots: Should we zero out rotations within a cluster? Helps with FCI solvers which should have zero gradients.\n\nReturns\n\ne: Energy\nU::Matrix: Orbital rotation matrix from input to output orbitals\nd1::RDM1: Optimized 1RDM in the optimized orbital basis\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.cmf_oo_diis"},{"category":"method","location":"library/CMFs/#TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.cmf_oo_gd-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{InCoreInts{T}, Vector{MOCluster}, Any, TPSChem.RDM.RDM1{T}}} where T","page":"CMF","text":"cmf_oo_gd( ints_in::InCoreInts{T}, clusters::Vector{MOCluster}, fspace, dguess::RDM1{T}; \n                maxiter_oo      = 100, \n                maxiter_ci      = 100, \n                maxiter_d1      = 100, \n                tol_oo          = 1e-6, \n                tol_d1          = 1e-7, \n                tol_ci          = 1e-8, \n                verbose         = 0, \n                alpha           = .1,\n                zero_intra_rots = true,\n                sequential      = false) where T\n\nDo CMF with orbital optimization\n\nArguments\n\nints::InCoreInts: integrals for full system\nclusters::Vector{MOCluster}: vector of cluster objects\nfspace::Vector{Vector{Integer}}: vector of particle number occupations for each cluster specifying the sectors of fock space \ndguess: initial guess for 1particle density matrix\nmaxiter_oo: Max iter for the orbital optimization iterations \nmaxiter_d1: Max iter for the cmf iteration for the 1RDM \nmaxiter_ci: Max iter for the CI diagonalization of the cluster states \ntol_oo: Convergence threshold for change in orbital gradient \ntol_ci: Convergence threshold for the cluster CI problems \ntol_d1: Convergence threshold for the CMF 1RDM \nsequential: If true use the density matrix of the previous cluster in a cMF iteration to form effective integrals. Improves comvergence, may depend on cluster orderings   \nverbose: Printing level \n\nReturns\n\ne: Energy\nU::Matrix: Orbital rotation matrix from input to output orbitals\nd1::RDM1: Optimized 1RDM in the optimized orbital basis\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.cmf_oo_gd"},{"category":"method","location":"library/CMFs/#TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.compute_cmf_energy-Tuple{Molecule, Matrix, Any, Any, Any}","page":"CMF","text":"compute_cmf_energy(mol::Molecule, C::Matrix, rdm1s, rdm2s, clusters)\n\nCompute the energy of a cluster-wise product state (CMF), specified by a list of 1 and 2 particle rdms local to each cluster\n\n#Arguments\n\nmol::Molecule\nC::Matrix: MO coefficients\nrdm1s: dictionary (ci.idx => Array) of 1rdms from each cluster (spin summed)\nrdm2s: dictionary (ci.idx => Array) of 2rdms from each cluster (spin summed)\nclusters::Vector{MOCluster}: vector of cluster objects\n\nreturn the total CMF energy\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.compute_cmf_energy"},{"category":"method","location":"library/CMFs/#TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.orbital_gradient_numerical-Tuple{Any, Any, Any, Any, TPSChem.RDM.RDM1}","page":"CMF","text":"orbital_gradient_numerical(ints, clusters, kappa, fspace, da, db; \n                                gconv = 1e-8, \n                                verbose = 1,\n                                stepsize = 1e-6)\n\nCompute orbital gradient with finite difference\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.orbital_gradient_numerical"},{"category":"method","location":"library/CMFs/#TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.orbital_objective_function-Tuple{Any, Any, Any, Any, TPSChem.RDM.RDM1}","page":"CMF","text":"orbital_objective_function(ints, clusters, kappa, fspace, da, db; \n                                ci_conv     = 1e-9,\n                                sequential  = false,\n                                verbose     = 1)\n\nObjective function to minimize in OO-CMF\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.orbital_objective_function"},{"category":"method","location":"library/CMFs/#TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.pack_gradient-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"CMF","text":"pack_gradient(K,norb)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.pack_gradient"},{"category":"method","location":"library/CMFs/#TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.unpack_gradient-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"CMF","text":"unpack_gradient(kappa,norb)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.ClusterMeanField.unpack_gradient"},{"category":"method","location":"library/CMFs/#TPSChem.QCBase.compute_energy-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{InCoreInts{T}, Dict{Integer, TPSChem.RDM.RDM1{T}}, Dict{Integer, TPSChem.RDM.RDM2{T}}, Vector{MOCluster}}} where T","page":"CMF","text":"QCBase.compute_energy(ints::InCoreInts{T}, rdm1s::Dict{Integer,RDM1{T}}, rdm2s::Dict{Integer,RDM2{T}}, clusters::Vector{MOCluster}; verbose=0) where T\n\nCompute the energy of a cluster-wise product state (CMF), specified by a list of 1 and 2 particle rdms local to each cluster. This method uses the full system integrals.\n\nints::InCoreInts: integrals for full system\nrdm1s: dictionary (ci.idx => RDM1) of 1rdms from each cluster\nrdm2s: dictionary (ci.idx => RDM2) of 2rdms from each cluster\nclusters::Vector{MOCluster}: vector of cluster objects\n\nreturn the total CMF energy\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.QCBase.compute_energy"},{"category":"section","location":"library/ClusteredTerms/","page":"ClusteredTerms","text":"Pages = [\"ClusteredTerms.md\"]","title":"ClusteredTerms"},{"category":"section","location":"library/ClusteredTerms/#ClusteredTerms","page":"ClusteredTerms","text":"","title":"ClusteredTerms"},{"category":"section","location":"library/outline/#Library-Outline","page":"-","text":"Pages = [\"public.md\", \"internals.md\", \"function_index.md\"]","title":"Library Outline"},{"category":"section","location":"library/function_index/#main-index","page":"-","text":"Pages = [\"public.md\", \"internals.md\", \"function_index.md\"]","title":"Index"},{"category":"section","location":"fci/#Simple-(and-slow)-FCI-Calculation-(FCI)","page":"Simple (and slow) FCI Calculation (FCI)","text":"In this example, we cluster a sequence of H<sub>2</sub> molecules","title":"Simple (and slow) FCI Calculation (FCI)"},{"category":"section","location":"fci/#First-create-a-molecule","page":"Simple (and slow) FCI Calculation (FCI)","text":"using TPSChem\n\natoms = []\npush!(atoms,Atom(1,\"H\",[0,0,0]))\npush!(atoms,Atom(2,\"H\",[0,0,1]))\npush!(atoms,Atom(3,\"H\",[0,0,2]))\npush!(atoms,Atom(4,\"H\",[0,0,3]))\npush!(atoms,Atom(5,\"H\",[0,0,4]))\npush!(atoms,Atom(6,\"H\",[0,0,5]))\nbasis = \"sto-3g\"\n\nNow create a PySCF object for creating integrals, and run FCI with 3 alpha and 3 beta electrons\n\nmol  = Molecule(0,1,atoms)\nmf   = TPSChem.pyscf_do_scf(mol,basis)\nints = TPSChem.pyscf_build_ints(mf.mol,mf.mo_coeff);\n\nna = 3\nnb = 3\ne_fci, d1_fci, d2_fci = TPSChem.pyscf_fci(ints,na,nb)\nC = mf.mo_coeff\nrdm_mf = C[:,1:2] * C[:,1:2]'\n\nCreate an FCIProblem object containing problem data\n\nnorbs = size(ints.h1)[1]\n\nproblem = StringCI.FCIProblem(norbs, 4, 4)\n\nNow run the CI code. This seems to be about 10x slower than pyscf at the moment, and only uses lanczos instead of a preconditioned solver \n\nStringCI.run_fci(ints, problem)","title":"First create a molecule"},{"category":"section","location":"library/Internals/#Internals","page":"Internals","text":"Pages = [\"Internals.md\"]","title":"Internals"},{"category":"section","location":"library/Internals/#Clusters","page":"Internals","text":"Clusters are simply collections of orbitals.","title":"Clusters"},{"category":"section","location":"library/Internals/#Hamiltonians","page":"Internals","text":"These are types/methods to handle the fermionic Hamiltonian","title":"Hamiltonians"},{"category":"section","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSCI","page":"TPSCI","text":"","title":"TPSCI"},{"category":"section","location":"library/TPSCI/#Background","page":"TPSCI","text":"Tensor Product Selected CI (TPSCI) approximates FCI on large active spaces using a sparse basis of tensor products of many-body cluster states. The main idea is fold much of the electron correlation up into the basis vectors themselves, by diagonalizing local Hamiltonians (Hamiltonians acting on disjoint sets of orbitals, \"clusters\"),  and using the tensor product space of these cluster states as our basis.  For entangled clusters, the convergence of the global energy with the number of local cluster states is slow, making direct truncation of the cluster basis ineffective.  However, instead of seeking a simple trunctation based on local information,  we seek a sparse representation, such that only a small number of global states are needed to obtain an accurate approximation of the ground state. ","title":"Background"},{"category":"section","location":"library/TPSCI/#Algorithm","page":"TPSCI","text":"The algorithm consists of the following steps:\n\nCMF: Optimize both orbitals and cluster ground states to obtain the variationally best single tensor product state wavefunction.\nCompute basis: Compute up to M excited states in each Fock sector desired (defaults to all) for each cluster.   These are excited states of the CMF Hamiltonian, which is an effective 1-cluster Hamiltonian containing the 1RDM contributions from all other clusters.\nForm operators: Compute matrix representations of all the 1, 2, and 3 creation/annihilation operator strings in the CMF cluster basis. E.g.:\nGamma_p^dagger qbarr^IJ = leftIright hatp^dagger hatqhatbarrleft Jright\nwhere I and J are cluster states on the same cluster, with well defined particle number and spin-projection. \nInitialize iterations: Set iteration counter to zero (n=0).  Initialize TPSCI state with CMF wavefunction, in the current mathcalP-space basis lbrace leftP_i^0rightrbrace, with the orthogonal complement defining the mathcalQ-space, lbrace leftQ_i^0rightrbrace.\nIterate Selected CI: \nDiagonalize hatH in the current mathcalP-space, lbrace leftP_i^nrightrbrace\nhatP^nhatHleftpsi^(0)_nright = E_nleftpsi^(0)_nright\nForm PT1 wavefunction by applying the Hamiltonian to the current variational state \nleftpsi^(1)_nright = hatRleftpsi^(0)_nright = sum_i c_i^(1)leftQ_i^nright\nwhere, hatR is the relevant resolvant. \nSelect from  leftpsi^(1)_nright the coefficients with magnitude larger than thresh_cipsi and add to mathcalP space:\nlbraceleftQ^n_irightrbrace xrightarrowc_i^(1)  epsilonlbraceleftP^n+1_jrightrbrace ","title":"Algorithm"},{"category":"section","location":"library/TPSCI/#Tips-on-clustering","page":"TPSCI","text":"","title":"Tips on clustering"},{"category":"section","location":"library/TPSCI/#Performance-considerations","page":"TPSCI","text":"Robust integral screening\nthresh_asci \nHOSVD boot-strapping","title":"Performance considerations"},{"category":"section","location":"library/TPSCI/#Index","page":"TPSCI","text":"Pages = [\"TPSCI.md\"]","title":"Index"},{"category":"section","location":"library/TPSCI/#Documentation","page":"TPSCI","text":"","title":"Documentation"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.contract_matrix_element-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ClusteredTerm1B{T}, Array{TPSChem.ClusterOps{T}, 1}, FockConfig, ClusterConfig, FockConfig, ClusterConfig}} where T","page":"TPSCI","text":"contract_matrix_element(   term::ClusteredTerm1B, \n                                cluster_ops::Vector{ClusterOps{T}},\n                                fock_bra::FockConfig, bra::ClusterConfig, \n                                fock_ket::FockConfig, ket::ClusterConfig)\n\nContraction for local (1body) terms. No contraction is needed, just a lookup from the correct operator\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.contract_matrix_element"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.contract_matrix_element-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ClusteredTerm2B{T}, Array{TPSChem.ClusterOps{T}, 1}, FockConfig, ClusterConfig, FockConfig, ClusterConfig}} where T","page":"TPSCI","text":"contract_matrix_element(   term::ClusteredTerm2B, \n                                cluster_ops::Vector{ClusterOps{T}},\n                                fock_bra::FockConfig, bra::ClusterConfig, \n                                fock_ket::FockConfig, ket::ClusterConfig)\n\nForm TPSCI matrix element by contracting operators with integrals for 2body terms. \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.contract_matrix_element"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.contract_matrix_element-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ClusteredTerm3B{T}, Array{TPSChem.ClusterOps{T}, 1}, FockConfig, ClusterConfig, FockConfig, ClusterConfig}} where T","page":"TPSCI","text":"contract_matrix_element(   term::ClusteredTerm3B, \n                                cluster_ops::Vector{ClusterOps{T}},\n                                fock_bra::FockConfig, bra::ClusterConfig, \n                                fock_ket::FockConfig, ket::ClusterConfig)\n\nForm TPSCI matrix element by contracting operators with integrals for 3body terms. \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.contract_matrix_element"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.contract_matrix_element-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ClusteredTerm4B{T}, Array{TPSChem.ClusterOps{T}, 1}, FockConfig, ClusterConfig, FockConfig, ClusterConfig}} where T","page":"TPSCI","text":"contract_matrix_element(   term::ClusteredTerm4B, \n                                cluster_ops::Vector{ClusterOps{T}},\n                                fock_bra::FockConfig, bra::ClusterConfig, \n                                fock_ket::FockConfig, ket::ClusterConfig)\n\nForm TPSCI matrix element by contracting operators with integrals for 4body terms. \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.contract_matrix_element"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.contract_matvec-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{R}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ClusteredTerm1B, Vector{TPSChem.ClusterOps}, FockConfig{N}, FockConfig{N}, ClusterConfig{N}, StaticArraysCore.MVector{R, T}}} where {T, R, N}","page":"TPSCI","text":"contract_matvec(   term::ClusteredTerm1B, \n                                cluster_ops::Vector{ClusterOps},\n                                fock_bra::FockConfig{N}, \n                                fock_ket::FockConfig{N}, conf_ket::ClusterConfig{N}, coef_ket::MVector{R,T};\n                                thresh=1e-9) where {T,R,N}\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.contract_matvec"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.contract_matvec-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{R}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ClusteredTerm2B, Vector{TPSChem.ClusterOps}, FockConfig{N}, FockConfig{N}, ClusterConfig{N}, StaticArraysCore.MVector{R, T}}} where {T, R, N}","page":"TPSCI","text":"contract_matvec(   term::ClusteredTerm2B, \n                                cluster_ops::Vector{ClusterOps},\n                                fock_bra::FockConfig{N}, \n                                fock_ket::FockConfig{N}, conf_ket::ClusterConfig{N}, coef_ket::MVector{R,T};\n                                thresh=1e-9) where {T,R,N}\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.contract_matvec"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.contract_matvec-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{R}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ClusteredTerm3B, Vector{TPSChem.ClusterOps}, FockConfig{N}, FockConfig{N}, ClusterConfig{N}, StaticArraysCore.MVector{R, T}}} where {T, R, N}","page":"TPSCI","text":"contract_matvec(   term::ClusteredTerm3B, \n                                cluster_ops::Vector{ClusterOps},\n                                fock_bra::FockConfig{N}, \n                                fock_ket::FockConfig{N}, conf_ket::ClusterConfig{N}, coef_ket::MVector{R,T};\n                                thresh=1e-9, prescreen=true) where {T,R,N}\n\nThis version should only use M^2N^2 storage, and n^5 scaling n={MN}\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.contract_matvec"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.contract_matvec-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{R}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ClusteredTerm4B, Vector{TPSChem.ClusterOps}, FockConfig{N}, FockConfig{N}, ClusterConfig{N}, StaticArraysCore.MVector{R, T}}} where {T, R, N}","page":"TPSCI","text":"contract_matvec(   term::ClusteredTerm4B, \n                                cluster_ops::Vector{ClusterOps},\n                                fock_bra::FockConfig{N}, \n                                fock_ket::FockConfig{N}, conf_ket::ClusterConfig{N}, coef_ket::MVector{R,T};\n                                thresh=1e-9, prescreen=true) where {T,R,N}\n\nThis version should only use M^2N^2 storage, and n^5 scaling n={MN}\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.contract_matvec"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.contract_matvec_M3-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{R}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ClusteredTerm3B, Vector{TPSChem.ClusterOps}, FockConfig{N}, FockConfig{N}, ClusterConfig{N}, StaticArraysCore.MVector{R, T}}} where {T, R, N}","page":"TPSCI","text":"contract_matvec_M3(   term::ClusteredTerm3B, \n                                cluster_ops::Vector{ClusterOps},\n                                fock_bra::FockConfig{N}, \n                                fock_ket::FockConfig{N}, conf_ket::ClusterConfig{N}, coef_ket::MVector{R,T};\n                                thresh=1e-9) where {T,R,N}\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.contract_matvec_M3"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.contract_matvec_M4-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{R}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ClusteredTerm4B, Vector{TPSChem.ClusterOps}, FockConfig{N}, FockConfig{N}, ClusterConfig{N}, StaticArraysCore.MVector{R, T}}} where {T, R, N}","page":"TPSCI","text":"contract_matvec_M4(   term::ClusteredTerm4B, \n                                cluster_ops::Vector{ClusterOps},\n                                fock_bra::FockConfig{N}, \n                                fock_ket::FockConfig{N}, conf_ket::ClusterConfig{N}, coef_ket::MVector{R,T};\n                                thresh=1e-9) where {T,R,N}\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.contract_matvec_M4"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.upper_bound-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"TPSCI","text":"upper_bound(g1, g2; c::Float64=1.0)\n\nReturn upper bound on the size of matrix elements resulting from matrix multiply \n\nV[I,J] =  g1[i,I] * g2[i,J] * c \n\nmax(|V|) <= sum_i max|g1[i,:]| * max|g2[i,:]| * |c|\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.upper_bound"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.upper_bound-Tuple{Array{Float64, 3}, Any, Any, Any}","page":"TPSCI","text":"upper_bound(v::Array{Float64,3}, g1, g2, g3; c::Float64=1.0)\n\nReturn upper bound on the size of tensor elements resulting from the following contraction\n\nV[I,J,K] = v[i,j,k] * g1[i,I] * g2[j,J] * g3[k,K] \n\nmax(|V|) <= sum_ijk |v[ijk]| * |g1[i,:]|_8 * |g2[j,:]|_8 * |g3[k,:]|_8 * |c|\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.upper_bound"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.upper_bound-Tuple{Array{Float64, 4}, Vararg{Any, 4}}","page":"TPSCI","text":"upper_bound(v::Array{Float64,4}, g1, g2, g3, g4; c::Float64=1.0)\n\nReturn upper bound on the size of tensor elements resulting from the following contraction\n\nV[I,J,K,L] = v[i,j,k,l] * g1[i,I] * g2[j,J] * g3[k,K] * g4[l,L]\n\nmax(|V|) <= sum_ijkl |v[ijkl]| * |g1[i,:]|_8 * |g2[j,:]|_8 * |g3[k,:]|_8 * |g4[l,:]|_8\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.upper_bound"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.upper_bound-Tuple{Matrix{Float64}, Any, Any}","page":"TPSCI","text":"upper_bound(v::Array{Float64,2}, g1, g2; c::Float64=1.0)\n\nReturn upper bound on the size of tensor elements resulting from the following contraction\n\nV[I,J] = v[i,j] * g1[i,I] * g2[j,J] \n\nmax(|V|) <= sum_ij |v[ij]| * |g1[i,:]|_8 * |g2[j,:]|_8 * |c|\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.upper_bound"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.upper_bound2-Tuple{Array{Float64, 3}, Vararg{Any, 4}}","page":"TPSCI","text":"upper_bound2(v::Array{Float64,3}, g1, g2, g3, thresh; c::Float64=1.0)\n\nGet upper bound on the possible values \n\nmax(H_IJ(K)|_K <= sum_r (sum_pq vpqrs max(g1[p,:]) * max(g2[q,:]) * |c| ) * |g3(r,K)|\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.upper_bound2"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.upper_bound2-Tuple{Array{Float64, 4}, Vararg{Any, 5}}","page":"TPSCI","text":"upper_bound2(v::Array{Float64,4}, g1, g2, g3, g4, thresh; c::Float64=1.0)\n\nGet upper bound on the possible values \n\nmax(H_IJK(L)|_L <= sum_s (sum_pqr vpqrs max(g1[p,:]) * max(g2[q,:]) * max(g3[r,:]) * |c| ) * |g4(s,L)|\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.upper_bound2"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.build_H_qq-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, Any, ClusteredOperator}} where {T, N, R}","page":"TPSCI","text":"build_H_qq(ci_vector::TPSCIstate, cluster_ops, clustered_ham)\n\nBuild the symmetric dimq×dimq Hamiltonian matrix for the Q-space defined by ci_vector.\n\nUnlike build_full_H_parallel, each thread writes directly into its own row of H via a view (no per-job scratch copy), halving peak memory from 2×dimq²×8 B to 1×dimq²×8 B. Safe because each job owns a unique bra_idx row — no data race.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.build_H_qq"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.build_H_qq_sparse-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, Any, ClusteredOperator}} where {T, N, R}","page":"TPSCI","text":"build_H_qq_sparse(ci_vector::TPSCIstate, cluster_ops, clustered_ham)\n\nBuild a sparse symmetric dimq×dimq Hamiltonian for the Q-space defined by ci_vector.\n\nEach thread accumulates its own (I,J,V) triplet lists (no shared state, no locks), then the full set is merged and passed to sparse().  Peak memory is O(nnz) rather than O(dimq²), making this viable for dimq >> 160K where the dense builders OOM.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.build_H_qq_sparse"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.build_brdm-Tuple{TPSCIstate, Any, Any}","page":"TPSCI","text":"build_brdm(ci_vector::TPSCIstate, ci, dims)\n\nBuild block reduced density matrix for Cluster,  ci\n\nci_vector::TPSCIstate = input state\nci = Cluster type for whihch we want the BRDM\ndims = list of dimensions for each fock sector\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.build_brdm"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.build_full_H-Tuple{TPSCIstate, Any, ClusteredOperator}","page":"TPSCI","text":"build_full_H(ci_vector::TPSCIstate, cluster_ops, clustered_ham::ClusteredOperator)\n\nBuild full TPSCI Hamiltonian matrix in space spanned by ci_vector. This works in serial for the full matrix\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.build_full_H"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.build_full_H_parallel-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, Any, ClusteredOperator}} where {T, N, R}","page":"TPSCI","text":"build_full_H_parallel(ci_vector::TPSCIstate, cluster_ops, clustered_ham::ClusteredOperator)\n\nBuild full TPSCI Hamiltonian matrix in space spanned by ci_vector. This works in serial for the full matrix\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.build_full_H_parallel"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.compute_diagonal!-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{Any, TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, Any, ClusteredOperator}} where {T, N, R}","page":"TPSCI","text":"compute_diagonal!(Hd, vector::TPSCIstate{T,N,R}, cluster_ops, clustered_ham) where {T,N,R}\n\nForm the diagonal of the hamiltonan, clustered_ham, in the basis defined by vector\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.compute_diagonal!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.compute_diagonal!-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{Any, TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, Any, String}} where {T, N, R}","page":"TPSCI","text":"compute_diagonal!(Hd, vector::TPSCIstate{T,N,R}, cluster_ops, opstring::String) where {T,N,R}\n\nFast version, used for PT2, overwrites Hd data with diagonal.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.compute_diagonal!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.compute_diagonal-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, Any, ClusteredOperator}} where {T, N, R}","page":"TPSCI","text":"compute_diagonal(vector::TPSCIstate{T,N,R}, cluster_ops, clustered_ham) where {T,N,R}\n\nForm the diagonal of the hamiltonan, clustered_ham, in the basis defined by vector\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.compute_diagonal"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.compute_diagonal-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, Any, String}} where {T, N, R}","page":"TPSCI","text":"compute_diagonal(vector::TPSCIstate{T,N,R}, cluster_ops, opstring::String) where {T,N,R}\n\nFast version, used for PT2\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.compute_diagonal"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.compute_expectation_value-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, Any, ClusteredOperator}} where {T, N, R}","page":"TPSCI","text":"compute_expectation_value(ci_vector::TPSCIstate{T,N,R}, cluster_ops, clustered_ham::ClusteredOperator; nbody=4) where {T,N,R}\n\nCompute expectation value of a ClusteredOperator (clustered_ham) for state ci_vector\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.compute_expectation_value"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.compute_expectation_value_parallel-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, Any, ClusteredOperator}} where {T, N, R}","page":"TPSCI","text":"function compute_expectation_value_parallel(ci_vector::TPSCIstate{T,N,R}, cluster_ops, clustered_ham::ClusteredOperator) where {T,N,R}\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.compute_expectation_value_parallel"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.expand_each_fock_space!-Union{Tuple{A}, Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, Array{ClusterBasis{A, T}, 1}}} where {T, N, R, A}","page":"TPSCI","text":"expand_each_fock_space!(s::TPSCIstate{T,N,R}, bases::Vector{ClusterBasis}) where {T,N,R}\n\nFor each fock space sector defined, add all possible basis states\n\nbasis::Vector{ClusterBasis} \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.expand_each_fock_space!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.expand_to_full_space!-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{A}, Tuple{TPSChem.AbstractState, Array{ClusterBasis{A, T}, 1}, Any, Any}} where {A, T}","page":"TPSCI","text":"expand_to_full_space!(s::AbstractState, bases::Vector{ClusterBasis}, na, nb)\n\nDefine all possible fock space sectors and add all possible basis states\n\nbasis::Vector{ClusterBasis} \nna: Number of alpha electrons total\nnb: Number of alpha electrons total\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.expand_to_full_space!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.hosvd-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, Any}} where {T, N, R}","page":"TPSCI","text":"hosvd(ci_vector::TPSCIstate{T,N,R}, cluster_ops; hshift=1e-8, truncate=-1) where {T,N,R}\n\nPeform HOSVD aka Tucker Decomposition of TPSCIstate\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.hosvd"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.matvec_H_qq-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, Any, ClusteredOperator, Vector{T}}} where {T, N, R}","page":"TPSCI","text":"matvec_H_qq(ci_vector::TPSCIstate, cluster_ops, clustered_ham, v) -> Vector\n\nApply Hqq to v without storing Hqq.\n\nStructurally identical to build_H_qq_sparse but instead of accumulating COO triplets, each thread accumulates H{bra,ket}×v[ket] and H{ket,bra}×v[bra] directly into a per-thread result buffer. Peak memory is O(nthreads × dimq) — a few hundred MB for dimq=262K — making this viable when both the sparse builder and openmatvecthread OOM.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.matvec_H_qq"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.project_out!-Tuple{TPSCIstate, TPSCIstate}","page":"TPSCI","text":"project_out!(v::TPSCIstate, w::TPSCIstate)\n\nProject w out of v      |v'> = |v> - |w><w|v>\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.project_out!"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.tps_ci_davidson-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, Any, ClusteredOperator}} where {T, N, R}","page":"TPSCI","text":"tps_ci_davidson(ci_vector::TPSCIstate{T,N,R}, cluster_ops, clustered_ham::ClusteredOperator) where {T,N,R}\n\nSolve for eigenvectors/values in the basis defined by ci_vector. Use iterative davidson solver.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.tps_ci_davidson"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.tps_ci_direct-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, Any, ClusteredOperator}} where {T, N, R}","page":"TPSCI","text":"function tps_ci_direct( ci_vector::TPSCIstate{T,N,R}, cluster_ops, clustered_ham::ClusteredOperator;\n                    H_old    = nothing,\n                    v_old    = nothing,\n                    verbose   = 0) where {T,N,R}\n\nSolve for eigenvectors/values in the basis defined by ci_vector. Use direct diagonalization.\n\nIf updating existing matrix, pass in Hold/vold to avoid rebuilding that block\n\nArguments\n\nsolver: Which solver to use. Options = [\"davidson\", \"krylovkit\"]\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.tps_ci_direct"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.tps_ci_matvec-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, Any, ClusteredOperator}} where {T, N, R}","page":"TPSCI","text":"tps_ci_matvec(ci_vector::TPSCIstate{T,N,R}, cluster_ops, clustered_ham::ClusteredOperator) where {T,N,R}\n\nCompute the action of clustered_ham on ci_vector.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.tps_ci_matvec"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.tpsci_cepa_solve-Union{Tuple{R2}, Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, Vector, TPSCIstate{T, N, R2}, Any, Any}, Tuple{TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, Vector, TPSCIstate{T, N, R2}, Any, Any, Any}, Tuple{TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, Vector, TPSCIstate{T, N, R2}, Vararg{Any, 4}}} where {T, N, R, R2}","page":"TPSCI","text":"tpsci_cepa_solve(ref_vector, e0, cepa_vector, cluster_ops, clustered_ham, cepa_shift, cepa_mit; tol, verbose)\n\nMulti-root CEPA solver for TPSCIstate.\n\nArguments\n\nref_vector: pre-solved reference state (R roots)\ne0: reference energies for each root (length R, pre-computed by caller)\ncepa_vector: shared FOIS — union of all roots' first-order interacting spaces\ncluster_ops, clustered_ham: operators\ncepa_shift: \"cepa\" (CEPA-0), \"acpf\", \"aqcc\", \"cisd\"\ncepa_mit: max CEPA iterations (only relevant for acpf/aqcc)\n\nThe amplitude equation for each root I is solved independently with the shared Hxx:     (Hxx - (E0[I] + shift[I])) * Cx[I] = -h[I]     E[I] = E0[I] + Cx[I]' * h[I]\n\nwhere h[I] = <Q|H|A_I> (coupling vector for root I).\n\nFully matrix-free: never builds H_xx explicitly.\n\nh[I] is computed by applying H to |AI> via openmatvec_thread then projecting to Q.\nCG matvec Hxx*v uses the same openmatvec_thread + Q-projection.\n\nThis scales to Qdim ~ 10^6 with O(Qdim) memory.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.tpsci_cepa_solve"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.contract_matvec_thread-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{R}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ClusteredTerm1B{T}, Array{TPSChem.ClusterOps{T}, 1}, FockConfig{N}, FockConfig{N}, ClusterConfig{N}, StaticArraysCore.MVector{R, T}, Any, Array{Vector{T}, 1}, Vector{Vector{Int16}}, Array{StaticArraysCore.MVector{N, Int16}, 1}}} where {T, R, N}","page":"TPSCI","text":"contract_matvec_thread(   term::ClusteredTerm1B, \n                                cluster_ops::Vector{ClusterOps},\n                                fock_bra::FockConfig{N}, \n                                fock_ket::FockConfig{N}, conf_ket::ClusterConfig{N}, coef_ket::MVector{R,T},\n                                sig, \n                                scr_f::Vector{Vector{T}},  \n                                scr_i::Vector{Vector{Int16}},  \n                                scr_m::Vector{MVector{N,Int16}};  \n                                thresh=1e-9) where {T,R,N}\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.contract_matvec_thread"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.contract_matvec_thread-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{R}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ClusteredTerm2B{T}, Array{TPSChem.ClusterOps{T}, 1}, FockConfig{N}, FockConfig{N}, ClusterConfig{N}, StaticArraysCore.MVector{R, T}, Any, Array{Vector{T}, 1}, Vector{Vector{Int16}}, Array{StaticArraysCore.MVector{N, Int16}, 1}}} where {T, R, N}","page":"TPSCI","text":"contract_matvec_thread(   term::ClusteredTerm2B, \n                                cluster_ops::Vector{ClusterOps},\n                                fock_bra::FockConfig{N}, \n                                fock_ket::FockConfig{N}, conf_ket::ClusterConfig{N}, coef_ket::MVector{R,T},\n                                sig, \n                                scr_f::Vector{Vector{T}},  \n                                scr_i::Vector{Vector{Int16}},  \n                                scr_m::Vector{MVector{N,Int16}};  \n                                thresh=1e-9) where {T,R,N}\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.contract_matvec_thread"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.contract_matvec_thread-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{R}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ClusteredTerm3B{T}, Array{TPSChem.ClusterOps{T}, 1}, FockConfig{N}, FockConfig{N}, ClusterConfig{N}, StaticArraysCore.MVector{R, T}, Any, Array{Vector{T}, 1}, Vector{Vector{Int16}}, Array{StaticArraysCore.MVector{N, Int16}, 1}}} where {T, R, N}","page":"TPSCI","text":"contract_matvec_thread(   term::ClusteredTerm3B, \n                                cluster_ops::Vector{ClusterOps},\n                                fock_bra::FockConfig{N}, \n                                fock_ket::FockConfig{N}, conf_ket::ClusterConfig{N}, coef_ket::MVector{R,T},\n                                sig, \n                                scr_f::Vector{Vector{T}},  \n                                scr_i::Vector{Vector{Int16}},  \n                                scr_m::Vector{MVector{N,Int16}};  \n                                thresh=1e-9, prescreen=true) where {T,R,N}\n\nThis version should only use M^2N^2 storage, and n^4 scaling n={MN}\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.contract_matvec_thread"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.contract_matvec_thread-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{R}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSChem.ClusteredTerm4B{T}, Array{TPSChem.ClusterOps{T}, 1}, FockConfig{N}, FockConfig{N}, ClusterConfig{N}, StaticArraysCore.MVector{R, T}, Any, Array{Vector{T}, 1}, Vector{Vector{Int16}}, Array{StaticArraysCore.MVector{N, Int16}, 1}}} where {T, R, N}","page":"TPSCI","text":"contract_matvec_thread(   term::ClusteredTerm4B, \n                                cluster_ops::Vector{ClusterOps},\n                                fock_bra::FockConfig{N}, \n                                fock_ket::FockConfig{N}, conf_ket::ClusterConfig{N}, coef_ket::MVector{R,T},\n                                sig, \n                                scr_f::Vector{Vector{T}},  \n                                scr_i::Vector{Vector{Int16}},  \n                                scr_m::Vector{MVector{N,Int16}};  \n                                thresh=1e-9, prescreen=true) where {T,R,N}\n\nThis version should only use M^2N^2 storage, and n^5 scaling n={MN}\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.contract_matvec_thread"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.open_matvec_thread-Union{Tuple{R}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TPSCIstate{T, N, R}, Any, Any}} where {T, N, R}","page":"TPSCI","text":"open_matvec_thread(ci_vector::TPSCIstate{T,N,R}, cluster_ops, clustered_ham; thresh=1e-9, nbody=4) where {T,N,R}\n\nCompute the action of the Hamiltonian on a tpsci state vector. Open here, means that we access the full FOIS  (restricted only by thresh), instead of the action of H on v within a subspace of configurations.  This is essentially used for computing a PT correction outside of the subspace, or used for searching in TPSCI.\n\nThis parallellizes over FockConfigs in the output state, so it's not the most fine-grained, but it avoids data races in  filling the final vector\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.open_matvec_thread"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.upper_bound2_thread-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Array{T, 3}, Any, Any, Any, Array{Vector{T}, 1}, Vector{Vector{Int16}}, Any}} where T","page":"TPSCI","text":"upper_bound2_thread(v::Array{T,4}, g1, g2, g3, \n    scr_f::Vector{Vector{T}}, scr_i::Vector{Vector{Int16}}, thresh; \n    c::T=1.0)\n\nmax(H_IJ(K)|_K <= sum_s (sum_pqr vpqrs max(g1[p,:]) * max(g2[q,:]) * |c| ) * |g3(r,K)|\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.upper_bound2_thread"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.upper_bound2_thread-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Array{T, 4}, Any, Any, Any, Any, Array{Vector{T}, 1}, Vector{Vector{Int16}}, Any}} where T","page":"TPSCI","text":"upper_bound2_thread(v::Array{T,4}, g1, g2, g3, g4, \n    scr_f::Vector{Vector{T}}, scr_i::Vector{Vector{Int16}}, thresh; \n    c::T=1.0)\n\nmax(H_IJK(L)|_L <= sum_s (sum_pqr vpqrs max(g1[p,:]) * max(g2[q,:]) * max(g3[r,:]) * |c| ) * |g4(s,L)|\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.upper_bound2_thread"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.upper_bound_thread-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{AbstractArray{T, 3}, Vararg{Any, 6}}} where T","page":"TPSCI","text":"upper_bound_thread(v::AbstractArray{T,3}, g1, g2, g3, scr1, scr2, scr3; c::T=1.0)\n\nReturn upper bound on the size of tensor elements resulting from the following contraction\n\nV[I,J,K] = v[i,j,k] * g1[i,I] * g2[j,J] * g3[k,K] \n\nmax(|V|) <= sum_ijk |v[ijk]| * |g1[i,:]|_8 * |g2[j,:]|_8 * |g3[k,:]|_8\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.upper_bound_thread"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.upper_bound_thread-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Any, Any}} where T","page":"TPSCI","text":"upper_bound_thread(g1, g2; c::T=1.0)\n\nReturn upper bound on the size of matrix elements resulting from matrix multiply \n\nV[I,J] =  g1[i,I] * g2[i,J] * c \n\nmax(|V|) <= sum_i max|g1[i,:]| * max|g2[i,:]| * |c|\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.upper_bound_thread"},{"category":"method","location":"library/TPSCI/#TPSChem.upper_bound_thread-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Array{T, 4}, Vararg{Any, 8}}} where T","page":"TPSCI","text":"upper_bound_thread(v::Array{T,4}, g1, g2, g3, g4, scr1, scr2, scr3, scr4; c::T=1.0)\n\nReturn upper bound on the size of tensor elements resulting from the following contraction\n\nV[I,J,K,L] = v[i,j,k,l] * g1[i,I] * g2[j,J] * g3[k,K] * g4[l,L]\n\nmax(|V|) <= sum_ijkl |v[ijkl]| * |g1[i,:]|_8 * |g2[j,:]|_8 * |g3[k,:]|_8 * |g4[l,:]|_8\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.upper_bound_thread"},{"category":"section","location":"library/TPSChem/","page":"TPSChem","text":"Pages = [\"TPSChem.md\"]","title":"TPSChem"},{"category":"section","location":"library/TPSChem/#TPSChem","page":"TPSChem","text":"","title":"TPSChem"},{"category":"section","location":"library/Utils/","page":"Utils","text":"Pages = [\"Utils.md\"]","title":"Utils"},{"category":"section","location":"library/Utils/#Utils","page":"Utils","text":"","title":"Utils"},{"category":"method","location":"library/Utils/#TPSChem.bubble_sort-Tuple{Any}","page":"Utils","text":"function bubble_sort(inp)\n\nSort inp (stable)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.bubble_sort"},{"category":"method","location":"library/Utils/#TPSChem.get_nchk-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Utils","text":"replace this with table lookup\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.get_nchk"},{"category":"section","location":"#TPSChem","page":"Home","text":"","title":"TPSChem"},{"category":"section","location":"library/public/#Public-Documentation","page":"Public Documentation","text":"Documentation for TPSChem.jl's public interface.\n\nSee the Internals section of the manual for internal package docs covering all submodules.","title":"Public Documentation"},{"category":"section","location":"library/public/#TPSChem","page":"Public Documentation","text":"","title":"TPSChem"},{"category":"module","location":"library/public/#TPSChem.TPSChem","page":"Public Documentation","text":"TPSChem: electronic structure in a tensor product state (TPS) basis.\n\nConsolidates the former FermiCG ecosystem (FermiCG, QCBase, InCoreIntegrals, BlockDavidson, RDM, ActiveSpaceSolvers, ClusterMeanField) into a single package. Each former package lives on as a submodule of the same name.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TPSChem.TPSChem"}]
}
